<T>__{cut to:}
<L>__{interior a bear baiting theater day}
<A>__{a small, open air theater where a chained bear is being led around the theater. a set of mastiffs are being led on the opposite side of the theater. the spectators are unruly, loudly making bets for the mauling to come. jonson is among them, taking a look at the bear, deciding whether to bet on it or not.}
<C>__{bear baiter}
<D>__{sampson! sired by the great arthur himself! no dog's yet been bred that can take him down!}
<A>__{shakespeare suddenly sits next jonson hardly notices.}
<C>__{shakespeare}
<D>__{i need more money.}
<C>__{jonson}
<D>__{more ? you already make more than any playwright bankside.}
<C>__{bear baiter}
